						<summary>

						<p>States that the chief <hi rend="bold">Nanni-chōḍa</hi> made a gift of the village of <hi rend="bold">Ḍēṅgarabūḍi</hi> and also a tank to the temple of Tribhuvana-Mallikārjuna-Mahādēva. The temple worshippers of Ḍēṅgarabūḍi were exempted from payment of duty on the sale of houses <hi rend="italic">(ammubaḍi suṅkhamu.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Face A.</p>						

